# Search Service Architecture

Use the official multi-entity search layer as the source of truth for read-time search behavior.

## Main files

- Core service: `humanupgradeapi/src/search/entitySearchService.ts`
- Per-entity config: `humanupgradeapi/src/search/entitySearchConfig.ts`
- Search input/result TS types: `humanupgradeapi/src/search/entitySearchTypes.ts`
- Searchable entity registry + embedding text source: `humanupgradeapi/src/search/embeddings/embeddingRegistry.ts`
- GraphQL contract: `humanupgradeapi/src/graphql/schema.graphql`
- GraphQL plural query delegation: `humanupgradeapi/src/graphql/resolvers/query.ts`
- Mutation-time embedding sync: `humanupgradeapi/src/services/searchableEntityWriteService.ts`

## GraphQL contract

- Every searchable model has explicit `ModelSearchInput`, `ModelSearchHit`, and `ModelSearchResult` types in `src/graphql/schema.graphql`
- Plural queries like `organizations`, `products`, and `episodes` now take `input` and return `{ items, total }`
- Clients only send `query`; GraphQL does not accept raw `embedding` input
- Singular queries remain direct record fetches and are not part of the search wrapper contract

## Mutation relationship

- The search service is read-only; it does not own create/update/delete behavior
- Mutation-time embedding refresh stays in `src/services/searchableEntityWriteService.ts` plus `src/search/embeddings/*`
- Top-level searchable mutations still use `embedding: EmbeddingWriteOptionsInput` with `AUTO`, `SKIP`, or `FORCE`

## Prisma usage

- `query.ts` passes `ctx.prisma` into the search service so reads stay request-scoped
- `NONE` mode uses Prisma delegate `findMany` + `count` with entity config filters and ordering
- Scored modes use Prisma raw SQL against `search_vector` and `embedding`, while hydration uses Prisma delegates to fetch records by ordered ids
- Dynamic table names come only from trusted entity config; user input stays in bound SQL parameters

## Scoring and ranking

- `LEXICAL`: PostgreSQL full-text search with `search_vector @@ websearch_to_tsquery('simple', query)` and `ts_rank_cd(...)`
- `SEMANTIC`: embed the incoming query with Bedrock using `inputType: 'search_query'`, then score with `1 - (embedding <=> query_vector)`
- `HYBRID`: take top 50 lexical candidates and top 50 semantic candidates, full-join by id, then compute `0.7 * lexical + 0.3 * semantic`
- Hybrid `total` is the union count from the top 200 lexical ids and top 200 semantic ids, not a full unbounded corpus count

## Change rules

- Keep GraphQL inputs explicit per model; do not collapse them into a discriminated union
- Keep scoring logic centralized in `entitySearchService.ts` and entity-specific filtering in `entitySearchConfig.ts`
- If you change searchable source fields, also check `embeddingRegistry.ts` and mutation-time embedding sync behavior

## Disclaimer

This documents the current API-side search architecture and is expected to evolve when the client app is created and real client search workflows force contract or ranking changes.
